    <h2>French Indochina</h2>
    <p>French have been in Southeast Asia for a while. Gave Nguyen Empire power. In the 1840s, seven missionaries were killed under a anti-christian emperor. Church leaders and Capitalist demanded military intervention. Napoleon III ordered his army to take over south Vietnam. After, the French took over Laos, Cambodia, and northern Vietnam, which they named French Indochina. Over time, the Vietnamese revolted and resisted the French.</p>
